[PlayAreaTiles]
<p>Click a tile to see the following info:</p>
<table>
<tr>
<td>
<div class="B">
<div class="H">(x,y)=(25,14)</div>
<table>
<tr>
<td><img alt="25,14" src="80ba38.png"/></td>
<td>
<i>Q_addr</i>=(x,#N181)=#N(46361), <i>Q</i>=#N24<br/>
<i>ref_addr</i>=(<i>Q</i>,y+#N160)=#N44568<br/>
<i>ref</i>=#N(186), <i>udg_page</i>=#N128<br/>
<i>udg_addr</i>=(<i>ref</i>,<i>udg_page</i>)=#N32954<br/>
<i>attr</i>=#N56
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>where:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<i>Q</i> is the 'Q value' for the tile (located at <i>Q_addr</i>)
</li>
<li>
<i>ref</i> is the UDG reference for the tile (located at <i>ref_addr</i>)
</li>
<li>
<i>udg_page</i> is the base page for the tile graphic data (#N(128), #N(136),
#N144 or #N152)
</li>
<li>
<i>udg_addr</i> is the base address of the tile graphic data
(<i>ref</i>+#N256*<i>udg_page</i>)
</li>
<li>
<i>attr</i> is the tile's attribute byte
</li>
</ul>
<p>
For an explanation of the Q value and how it is used to determine
<i>udg_page</i> and the attribute byte (<i>attr</i>) for a tile, see #R24684.
</p>
<p>
The eight graphic bytes for a tile are located thus:
</p>
<table class="default">
<tr><th>Address</th><th>Contents</th></tr>
<tr>
<td>(<i>ref</i>,<i>udg_page</i>)=<i>udg_addr</i></td>
<td>Graphic byte 1/8</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>(<i>ref</i>,<i>udg_page</i>+1)=<i>udg_addr</i>+#N256</td>
<td>Graphic byte 2/8</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>(<i>ref</i>,<i>udg_page</i>+2)=<i>udg_addr</i>+#N512</td>
<td>Graphic byte 3/8</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>(<i>ref</i>,<i>udg_page</i>+3)=<i>udg_addr</i>+#N768</td>
<td>Graphic byte 4/8</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>(<i>ref</i>,<i>udg_page</i>+4)=<i>udg_addr</i>+#N1024</td>
<td>Graphic byte 5/8</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>(<i>ref</i>,<i>udg_page</i>+5)=<i>udg_addr</i>+#N1280</td>
<td>Graphic byte 6/8</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>(<i>ref</i>,<i>udg_page</i>+6)=<i>udg_addr</i>+#N1536</td>
<td>Graphic byte 7/8</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>(<i>ref</i>,<i>udg_page</i>+7)=<i>udg_addr</i>+#N1792</td>
<td>Graphic byte 8/8</td>
</tr>
</table>
