[Page:AnimatoryStateTiles]
JavaScript=tiles.js
PageContent=#INCLUDE(AnimatoryStateTiles)

[AnimatoryStateTiles]
<div>
<p>Click a tile in the gallery below to see the following info:</p>
<table>
<tr>
<td>
<div class="B">
<div class="H">#N0: row 1, column 1</div>
<table>
<tr>
<td><img alt="#N0:1,1" src="b762.png"/></td>
<td>
<i>lsb</i>=#N(128), <i>ref_page</i>=#N220<br/>
<i>ref_addr</i>=(<i>lsb</i>,<i>ref_page</i>)=#N56448<br/>
<i>ref</i>=#N(98), <i>udg_page</i>=#N183<br/>
<i>udg_addr</i>=(<i>ref</i>,<i>udg_page</i>)=#N46946
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>where:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<i>lsb</i> is the animatory state + #N128 (#N128-#N255)
</li>
<li>
<i>ref_page</i> is the page containing the UDG reference for the tile
(#N215-#N226)
</li>
<li>
<i>ref_addr</i> is the address of the UDG reference
(<i>lsb</i>+#N256*<i>ref_page</i>)
</li>
<li>
<i>ref</i> is the UDG reference at <i>ref_addr</i> (#N(0), #N73-#N255)
</li>
<li>
<i>udg_page</i> is the base page for the tile graphic data (#N183 or #N199)
</li>
<li>
<i>udg_addr</i> is the base address of the tile graphic data
(<i>ref</i>+#N256*<i>udg_page</i>)
</li>
</ul>
<p>
The graphic for an animatory state is made up of 12 tiles in a 3x4 grid:
</p>
<table class="asgrid">
<tr><td>0</td><td>4</td><td>8</td></tr>
<tr><td>1</td><td>5</td><td>9</td></tr>
<tr><td>2</td><td>6</td><td>10</td></tr>
<tr><td>3</td><td>7</td><td>11</td></tr>
</table>
<p>
Each tile has a UDG reference (<i>ref</i>) located at (<i>lsb</i>,T+#N215),
where T is the tile number (0-11).
</p>
<p>
The eight graphic bytes and eight mask bytes for a tile are located thus:
</p>
<table class="default">
<tr><th>Address</th><th>Contents</th></tr>
<tr>
<td>(<i>ref</i>,<i>udg_page</i>)=<i>udg_addr</i></td>
<td>Graphic byte 1/8</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>(<i>ref</i>,<i>udg_page</i>+#N1)=<i>udg_addr</i>+#N256</td>
<td>Mask byte 1/8</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>(<i>ref</i>,<i>udg_page</i>+#N2)=<i>udg_addr</i>+#N512</td>
<td>Graphic byte 2/8</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>(<i>ref</i>,<i>udg_page</i>+#N3)=<i>udg_addr</i>+#N768</td>
<td>Mask byte 2/8</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>(<i>ref</i>,<i>udg_page</i>+#N4)=<i>udg_addr</i>+#N1024</td>
<td>Graphic byte 3/8</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>(<i>ref</i>,<i>udg_page</i>+#N5)=<i>udg_addr</i>+#N1280</td>
<td>Mask byte 3/8</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>(<i>ref</i>,<i>udg_page</i>+#N6)=<i>udg_addr</i>+#N1536</td>
<td>Graphic byte 4/8</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>(<i>ref</i>,<i>udg_page</i>+#N7)=<i>udg_addr</i>+#N1792</td>
<td>Mask byte 4/8</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>(<i>ref</i>,<i>udg_page</i>+#N8)=<i>udg_addr</i>+#N2048</td>
<td>Graphic byte 5/8</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>(<i>ref</i>,<i>udg_page</i>+#N9)=<i>udg_addr</i>+#N2304</td>
<td>Mask byte 5/8</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>(<i>ref</i>,<i>udg_page</i>+#N10)=<i>udg_addr</i>+#N2560</td>
<td>Graphic byte 6/8</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>(<i>ref</i>,<i>udg_page</i>+#N11)=<i>udg_addr</i>+#N2816</td>
<td>Mask byte 6/8</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>(<i>ref</i>,<i>udg_page</i>+#N12)=<i>udg_addr</i>+#N3072</td>
<td>Graphic byte 7/8</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>(<i>ref</i>,<i>udg_page</i>+#N13)=<i>udg_addr</i>+#N3328</td>
<td>Mask byte 7/8</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>(<i>ref</i>,<i>udg_page</i>+#N14)=<i>udg_addr</i>+#N3584</td>
<td>Graphic byte 8/8</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>(<i>ref</i>,<i>udg_page</i>+#N15)=<i>udg_addr</i>+#N3840</td>
<td>Mask byte 8/8</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>
The 'null' UDG (<i>ref</i>=#N0) is always taken to be blank (eight zeroes); its
graphic data is not looked up at (#N(0),#N183) or (#N(0),#N199).
</p>
<p>
Any given tile (identified by <i>udg_addr</i>) may appear in more than one
animatory state (and in more than one place in a single animatory state).
</p>
<p>
The tiles for animatory states #N128-#N255 are not stored separately; the tiles
for animatory state N>=#N128 are obtained by flipping the tiles for animatory
state N-#N128 (see #R24576).
</p>
</div>
